[{"id":"VR868727","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following correctly indicates the direction of the electric field at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi> </math></span></span> and provides a valid justification?</p>\n\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\">\n\t<colgroup>\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:30\" />\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:60\" />\n\t\t<col class=\"colspec align:left colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:270\" />\n\t</colgroup>\n\t<thead class=\"thead\">\n\t\t<tr class=\"row rowsep:1\">\n\t\t\t<th class=\"entry colname:col1\">&nbsp;</th>\n\t\t\t<th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Direction</th>\n\t\t\t<th class=\"entry colname:col3\">Justification</th>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</thead>\n\t<tbody class=\"tbody valign:middle\">\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows an arrow pointing upward and to the right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR868727.g03.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col3\">The electric field is directed perpendicular to the equipotential lines and toward decreasing electric potential.</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows an arrow pointing upward and to the right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR868727.g05.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col3\">The electric field is in the same direction as the electric force exerted on a negatively charged object.</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">C</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows an arrow pointing downward and to the left.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR868727.g07.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col3\">The electric field is directed perpendicular to the equipotential lines and toward increasing electric potential.</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">D</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows an arrow pointing downward and to the left.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR868727.g09.svg\" /></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col3\">The electric field is in the same direction as the electric force exerted on a positively charged object.</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n","rubricRef":"VR868727_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figure shows equipotential lines in a region containing three charged objects.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows equipotential lines in a region containing three charged objects that are arranged approximately like the vertices of an equilateral triangle with the two lower objects next to each other horizontally and the upper object directly above the halfway point between the two lower objects. Equipotential lines of negative 10 volts, negative 5 volts, and 0 volts loop around the upper object, going from inner to outer. An equipotential line of 5 volts curves between the upper and lower objects. Equipotential lines of 20 volts and 15 volts loop around each of the lower objects, going from inner to outer. An equipotential line of 10 volts loops around the two lower objects collectively. A point P is on the 10 volt equipotential line above and to the right of the lower left object on a section of the equipotential line that is sloping downward and to the right toward the area in the middle of the two lower objects.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR868727.g11.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">B</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">C</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">D</p>"],"answer":0}]